comments.body:
If you want to use `this.objects`as an array you should do something like that

``` javascript
    var  geometry = new THREE.CubeGeometry(10,10,10);

    var material =  new THREE.MeshLambertMaterial( { color:0xffffff, 
        map: THREE.ImageUtils.loadTexture( 'texture.jpg' ),
        shading: THREE.FlatShading } );

    this.objects = [];

    for ( var i = 0; i < 2; i ++ )
    {
        var mesh = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material );
        mesh.position.x = ( Math.random() - 0.5 ) * 100;
        mesh.position.y = ( Math.random() - 0.5 ) *100;
        mesh.position.z = ( Math.random() - 0.5 ) * 100;
        mesh.updateMatrix();
        mesh.matrixAutoUpdate = false;

        this.scene.add( mesh );
        this.objects.push( mesh );
    }
```

If it does not work better check that your `this` is still valid (beware of closure and local function that have thier own `this` in javascript)

