`MeshFaceMaterial` is just pass-through material, it doesn't do anything by itself, just tells renderer to use `geometry.materials` (which are initialized from JSON). 

So to get any visible change in materials that were created from JSON, you need to mess directly with them:

``` javascript
geometry.materials[ 0 ].morphTargets = true;
geometry.materials[ 0 ].morphNormals = true;
```

